🧠 ONE GOLDEN RULE (yaad rakh)

... ka matlab hota hai:
“context ke hisaab se ya to phaila do, ya jama kar do.”

Same dots, opposite kaam.

📦 SPREAD OPERATOR = PHAILA DO (OPEN KAR DO)

Soch ek bag hai.

const bag = ["apple", "banana", "orange"];

❌ Bag ko aise daal diya
basket.push(bag);


Result:

[ ["apple", "banana", "orange"] ]


❌ Bag ke andar bag
❌ Useless for use

✅ Bag khol ke daala (SPREAD)
basket.push(...bag);


Result:

["apple", "banana", "orange"]


👉 Yehi spread hai

Bag khol → items bahar

🧠 Jab bhi dekho:
...array


👉 dimag me bolo:

“Array ke andar jo hai, wo alag-alag nikaal do”

🔥 Tumhara code (dubara, slow motion)
createLogs(...)


Returns:

[
  {log1},
  {log2},
  {log3}
]


Ab:

logsToInsert.push(...createLogs(...));


Actually hota hai:

logsToInsert.push(
  {log1},
  {log2},
  {log3}
);


✔️ Correct
✔️ Flat array
✔️ Mongo happy

📥 REST OPERATOR = JAMA KAR DO (PACK KAR DO)

Ab ulta socho.
Bahut saare arguments aa rahe hain → ek box me jama karo.

Example
function demo(...items) {
  console.log(items);
}
demo(1,2,3,4);


Output:

[1,2,3,4]


👉 Matlab:

“Jo bhi aaye, sab ek array bana do”

🧠 Jab bhi dekho:
function fn(...args)


👉 dimag me bolo:

“Aane waali cheez ko pack kar raha hoon”

⚔️ SAME DOTS, OPPOSITE DIRECTION
Situation	... kya karta
Array ke aage	PHAILA
Function call me	PHAILA
Function params me	JAMA
Assignment ke left	JAMA
Assignment ke right	PHAILA

📌 Shortcut yaad rakh:

Right side → Spread
Left side → Rest

🎯 ONE-LINE MEMORY HOOK

Spread = “andar ka maal bahar”
Rest = “bahar ka maal andar”

Bas. Isse zyada simple nahi ho sakta.

🧪 Final brain test (slowly soch)
const fn = (...x) => x;
fn(...[10, 20, 30]);


Step-by-step:

...[10,20,30] → 10,20,30 (SPREAD)

(...x) → x = [10,20,30] (REST)

Agar ye clear hai → concept 100% locked 🔒

